{
  "stem": "5259.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was the speech of Hitler.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, it's-- we-- I know that, one day, because of the many anti-Semites that there were in Kalisz, because of the background of Volksdeutsche and German.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Being on the balcony, I saw people running and screaming, 'Jews out of Poland!' And it was so strange to me, I guess, and even in that age, to hear a Jew just being called a Jew.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because I never knew what a Jew means.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I knew that my parents were people living in Poland, like Poles.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I-- my-- it was a-- my mother light the candles, and this what I knew about, actually about Jewish upbringing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Nothing else, because-- maybe because of my age.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But the first thing what I felt, it was 1939. 1939, we were displaced right away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were sent out of the city to Lodz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We were walking, I remember, myself and my mother, because my father was taken to go to Warsaw, I think to defend Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This was, I think, an order or something.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we were walking by foot from Kalisz to Lodz, by foot and by, I think, in the beginning, we had a carriage.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then they took it away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And the Germans were flying their planes very, very low, and shooting.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I remember being in a forest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the bullets were flying around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the first thing that was my Jewish word that I heard from everybody else was, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[SOB] We survived that, came to Lodz, stayed for a long time in my uncle's apartment.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And after a short time-- I cannot tell times-- we came back to Kalisz back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And my father came back from Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And from then on it started.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
